Your _TextViews_ are placed inside a chain that is anchored to the parent&#39;s top and bottom with a default chain style of `spread` which is the default. (See [&quot;_Chain Style_&quot;](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/support/constraint/ConstraintLayout#chain-style).)

Change the chain style to `packed` and add a top margin of `8dp` to _TV\_max\_angle_.

    &lt;TextView
        android:id=&quot;@+id/TV_max_angle&quot;
        android:layout_width=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
        android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
        android:layout_marginTop=&quot;8dp&quot;
        android:layout_marginBottom=&quot;32dp&quot;
        android:text=&quot;@string/maximum_of_angle&quot;
        android:textAlignment=&quot;center&quot;
        android:textColor=&quot;@color/colorPrimaryDark2&quot;
        android:textSize=&quot;15sp&quot;
        android:textStyle=&quot;bold&quot;
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toTopOf=&quot;@+id/TV_current_angle&quot;
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf=&quot;parent&quot;
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf=&quot;parent&quot;
        app:layout_constraintTop_toTopOf=&quot;parent&quot;
        app:layout_constraintVertical_bias=&quot;0.0&quot;
        app:layout_constraintVertical_chainStyle=&quot;packed&quot; /&gt;

This produces the following layout:

[![enter image description here][1]][1]

You may need to adjust the location of the buttons, but this will eliminate the excess space at the top.

  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/1UJp9.png

